createConnection

public void createConnection(String[] parameters)
Creates a new connection.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] argument the name for the connection,
parameters[2] argument is the ip address of the server the clients connects to,
parameters[3] argument is the port the client connects to on the server,
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.

XTTProperties

startDiameterServer

public boolean startDiameterServer(String[] parameters)
starts the Diameterserver as an instance of DiameterServer.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] argument is the DiameterServer port,
parameters[2] is the DiameterServer root directory,
parameters[3] argument is the DiameterServer timeout.
If only parameters[0] is submitted the parameters will be taken from the configuration xml document in XTTProperties.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
DiameterServer, XTTProperties

stopDiameterServer

public boolean stopDiameterServer(String[] parameters)
stops all/one Diameterservers and all it's threads.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name, no additional parameters are requeired,
the optional parameters[1] argument is the DiameterServer port of the DiameterServer to stop, if omitted all running servers are stopped.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
DiameterServer.closeSocket(String), DiameterServer.closeSockets()

setPerWorkerDelay

public void setPerWorkerDelay(String[] parameters)
Sets a delay which will delay the response by delay*workerid miliseconds, nice if you know parallel connections get opened in order so you can keep the responses in order

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] is a delay which will delay the response by (delay*(workerid+1)) miliseconds.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
DiameterWorkerServer.setPerWorkerDelay(int)
